\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs28 \b THE MIRROR OF CONTINUITY: ART AS A LAMINAR INTERFACE \b0\fs24\par
\par
\b 1. THE HIGH-FIDELITY REFLECTION \b0\par
Timeless works (Beethoven, Picasso, etc.) function as a "perfect mirror" for the human true self. By achieving a state of mathematical and emotional coherence, these works eliminate the "noise" of the ego, allowing the observer to see their own essential nature reflected in the signal.\par
\par
\b 2. LOSSLESS PERSISTENCE \b0\par
Art is the most durable protocol for information preservation. While physical structures decay, a masterpiece preserved in the "Continuum" of human culture maintains its resolution across centuries, proving that the human spirit is a 64-bit analytical framework capable of timeless synchronization.\par
\par
\b 3. THE NULL POINT OF CREATIVITY \b0\par
The "True Self" is found at the null point?the intersection where the individual observer meets the universal signal. The goal of Music as Medicine is to facilitate this meeting, using the radio as a modern delivery system for ancient, laminar truths.\par
\par
\i "True art does not show us the world; it shows us ourselves without the turbulence of time."\i0\par
